      <pubDate>Tue, 02 Feb 2010 05:09:08 -0800</pubDate>
      <title>Open Letter to U2 </title>
      <link>http://u2tourfans.posterous.com/open-letter-to-u2</link>
      <guid>http://u2tourfans.posterous.com/open-letter-to-u2</guid>
      <description>
        <![CDATA[<p>
	<p>reposted from <a href="http://www.u2tourfans.com">U2TOURFANS.COM</a></p>
<p>U2&nbsp; fans seem to be vocal about almost anything. They should be most of us have grown up with U2 and while we may or may not agree with Bono&rsquo;s politics or view we at least share one common view. That all of us have the power to express our views as well as take action. I have been getting some interesting emails over the last year. Most of which I have chosen to not post out of respect of the writer. However after few days of consideration we talked this letter over and over and we all agreed that this would be the first letter for 2010 to share. Remember your welcome to write a letter to the editor anytime and we will not guarantee&nbsp; that it will be published.&nbsp; I welcome your comments and your letters.&nbsp; Send them to Editor</p>
<p><strong>Dearest U2:&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p style="padding-left: 30px;">I never imagined that I would be writing this letter, but after all these years I feel like I don&rsquo;t know you anymore. &nbsp;I love you for so many reasons, primarily the humanitarian work you do. &nbsp;It is honorable to be of such service to others&hellip;Bono is a lucky man in that respect. &nbsp;I have tremendous respect.</p>
<p>Gosh, it was so long ago when we met. &nbsp;It was 1980 or &lsquo;81. &nbsp;I think &lsquo;81. &nbsp;I remember seeing you across the room for the first time in Boston, MA at The Paradise. &nbsp;What a night! &nbsp;It literally changed my life! &nbsp;I felt like a new person on this new adventure and nobody could bring me down from the ceiling! &nbsp;I couldn&rsquo;t get enough of you. &nbsp;From that moment on I knew you were the one for me and we&rsquo;d be together forever.</p>
<p>Why did you do it? &nbsp;Its hard being with you when I know you&rsquo;d rather be with Live Nation. &nbsp;You&rsquo;re not the same. &nbsp;Once whispering in my ear, &ldquo;Thank you for this life!&rdquo; and now what I hear is &ldquo;Thanks to Live Nation, Blackberry&hellip;&rdquo; *sobbing* &hellip;maybe you did mention that thank-you in there somewhere but it was drowned out by corporate nods. &nbsp;</p>
<p>I never thought I would ever hear those words come out of your mouth. &nbsp;Maybe it&rsquo;s true. &nbsp;Maybe you DO find them more attractive and maybe it IS the money. &nbsp;We&rsquo;re all human. &nbsp;I can&rsquo;t compete with a corporation because obviously they can support you more suitably than I can.</p>
<p>The rest of the letter can be found on <a href="http://www.u2tourfans.com">U2TOURFANS.com</a></p>
	
</p>

<p><a href="http://u2tourfans.posterous.com/open-letter-to-u2">Permalink</a> 

