      <pubDate>Mon, 18 Jan 2010 05:38:03 -0800</pubDate>
      <title>In the Name of Love </title>
      <link>http://u2tourfans.posterous.com/in-the-name-of-love-8</link>
      <guid>http://u2tourfans.posterous.com/in-the-name-of-love-8</guid>
      <description>
        <![CDATA[<p>
	<p><span class="full-image-float-right ssNonEditable"><span><img src="/storage/DrMartinLutherKingJr.jpg?__SQUARESPACE_CACHEVERSION=1263820094292" alt="" style="" /></span><span class="thumbnail-caption" style="">Dr Martin Luther King </span></span></p>
<p><span class="full-image-float-right ssNonEditable"><span class="thumbnail-caption" style="">Vides and Full Story can befound on <a href="http://www.u2tourfans.com">u2tourfans</a><br /></span></span></p>
<p>This is a tribute to Martin Luther King, Jr. An exhibit dedicated to the civil rights leader was on display at the Chicago Peace Museum in 1983 when the band visited.</p>
<p>The song had been intended to be about Ronald Reagan's pride in America's military power but writer Bono had been influenced by Stephen B. Oates's book <em>Let The Trumpet Sound: A Life of Martin Luther King, Jr.</em> and a biography of Malcolm X.</p>
